						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. III) set up on the tank-bund.</p>						

						<p>Rāmachandrarāya [A.D. 1282].</p>						

						<p>This damaged and worn out inscription belongs to Rāmachandrarāya's regnal year 15, Chitrabhānu, Bhādrapada, • • • Sōmavāra. The date will correspond to some Monday between 6th August and 3rd September in A.D. 1282. In the absence of the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> it is difficult to be precise on this point.</p>						

						<p>It refers to a battle fought between <hi rend="italic">Nāḷprabhu</hi> • • • dēvarasa, the <hi rend="italic">manneya</hi> of Bandaḷike and • • (name lost) of Tarakū• It is stated that a person (name lost) ascended heaven during the fight. </p>						

						</summary>
